1. GOOGLE ML KIT — FACE MESH DETECTION & FACE DETECTION
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
This app uses Google ML Kit on-device APIs for face tracking, including:
  • ML Kit Face Mesh Detection (com.google.mlkit:face-mesh-detection)
  • ML Kit Face Detection (com.google.mlkit:face-detection)
Your use of ML Kit is governed by:
  • ML Kit Terms of Service
    https://developers.google.com/ml-kit/terms
  • Google APIs Terms of Service
    https://developers.google.com/terms
  • Google Privacy Policy (including metrics sent by ML Kit)
    https://policies.google.com/privacy
Important points (summary; the Google terms above prevail):
  • Processing of camera images for face mesh / face detection runs on-device.
    ML Kit does not send those images or face mesh outputs to Google servers
    for inference.
  • ML Kit may contact Google servers for updates, compatibility, bug fixes,
    and performance metrics, as described in Google’s documentation.
  • You may not reverse engineer or attempt to extract ML Kit models or
    source code except where applicable law expressly allows it.
  • Face Mesh Detection is a beta API and may change without backward
    compatibility guarantees.
Facial data in this app:
  • Face mesh and tracking are processed locally on the device.
  • The app does not upload face images, face meshes, or biometric templates
    to the developer’s servers.
  • User-created 3D photos/videos and saved items are stored in the app’s
    private local storage on the device unless the user explicitly exports
    or shares them.
You are responsible for informing end users about Google’s processing of
ML Kit metrics data where required by law (e.g. Google Play / App Store
data safety disclosures).
Open-source components bundled with ML Kit / related Google libraries may
be licensed under the Apache License 2.0. See Section 6 below.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2. DEPTH ANYTHING V2 — SMALL MODEL (DEPTH ESTIMATION)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
This app uses the monocular depth estimation model:
  • Depth Anything V2 — Small variant
  • Bundled file: depth_anything_v2_small_fp16.onnx
  • Inference via Microsoft ONNX Runtime for Android
The Depth-Anything-V2-Small model weights are licensed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0.
Source project:
  https://github.com/DepthAnything/Depth-Anything-V2
Project homepage / paper:
  https://depth-anything-v2.github.io/
License note from the upstream repository:
  • Depth-Anything-V2-Small → Apache License 2.0
  • Depth-Anything-V2-Base / Large / Giant → CC-BY-NC-4.0 (NOT used in this app)
This app uses ONLY the Small model (Apache-2.0). It does NOT ship Base,
Large, or Giant variants.
The ONNX file included in the app may be a converted/optimized build
(e.g. FP16) derived from the upstream Small checkpoint. Any such conversion
is a derivative work of the Small model and remains subject to Apache 2.0
and the attribution requirements below.
Suggested attribution (recommended in app “About” / store listing):
  “Depth maps powered by Depth Anything V2 (Small), © DepthAnything /
   contributors, licensed under Apache 2.0.”
